1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,160
THIS DRAMA IS CREATED
FOR ENTERTAINMENT PURPOSES

2
00:00:04,240 --> 00:00:07,600
ALL CHARACTERS, SETTINGS
AND EVENTS ARE ENTIRELY FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:07,680 --> 00:00:10,920
THERE IS NO INTENT TO REFERENCE
ANY ORGANIZATIONS OR INDIVIDUALS

4
00:03:07,400 --> 00:03:09,120
Dad!

5
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:10,760
Hold Mookda!

6
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,880
You can't help her anymore.

7
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:14,920
<i>If we run together,</i>
<i>none of us will make it. I'll cover you.</i>

8
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,720
I can't let her die yet.

9
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:21,080
So they want you to trade the lives
of the Seven Legends for Ms. Duangnet?

10
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,120
Sarge Dab isn't here.

11
00:03:28,200 --> 00:03:29,760
Huh? Dab what? Take this.

12
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:33,480
Run!

13
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:42,840
So that means Phoenix's deal
with Sergey didn't go smoothly.

14
00:03:42,920 --> 00:03:44,240
That's why he sent his right-hand man.

15
00:03:44,320 --> 00:03:48,880
So we have to stop this major
arms deal from going through.

16
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:55,720
Boss. I'm sorry, Boss.

17
00:03:56,640 --> 00:03:58,560
You'd better go find
something useful to do for Boss.

18
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:02,320
Right now,
your daughter's life depends on him.

19
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,200
Boss,

20
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:06,400
I've served you loyally all along.

21
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,840
Whatever my daughter did,

22
00:04:08,440 --> 00:04:11,560
let me take the blame instead.
Please spare my daughter's life, Boss.

23
00:04:11,640 --> 00:04:13,000
You know…

24
00:04:14,720 --> 00:04:16,000
that if I go soft

25
00:04:16,720 --> 00:04:20,399
and let some kid
walk all over me like this,

26
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:23,120
how am I supposed to stay on top?

27
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:25,640
Boss, please, I'm begging you.

28
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,720
They're both

29
00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:30,200
- useless to me now.
- Boss, no.

30
00:04:30,280 --> 00:04:32,440
- Mook. Boss, please.
- Take them away.

31
00:04:32,520 --> 00:04:35,680
- Dad. Dad.
- Mook. Mook. Boss, please.

32
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:08,600
You came alone?

33
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,280
Igor.

34
00:05:17,720 --> 00:05:21,720
So, did you take care
of your internal problem?

35
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,400
Mm.

36
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,480
From now on,
nothing will get in the way anymore.

37
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:29,320
Thanks for sending Igor to help.

38
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,080
It's just business.

39
00:05:34,920 --> 00:05:37,000
I don't want my first deal
to have any issues.

40
00:05:40,760 --> 00:05:42,640
At first, I thought Phoenix

41
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,760
was supposed to be professional.

42
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:51,320
I didn't expect a few lousy spies

43
00:05:51,400 --> 00:05:53,400
to mess things up this badly.

44
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,040
Hey.

45
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,320
Lousy?

46
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:01,560
I had to make sure
where the problem started

47
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,240
and fix it.

48
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,400
Now that you're here

49
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,800
and there are no Seven Legends in the way,

50
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:12,560
that proves
I'm the professional for this deal.

51
00:06:16,360 --> 00:06:18,880
You've checked the goods
we agreed on, haven't you?

52
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:22,080
All accounted for. Plenty of extras too.

53
00:06:22,720 --> 00:06:26,320
Who else in this region is ready to be
your number one partner like me?

54
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:27,960
Nah.

55
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,440
I want to see it on the site again.

56
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:32,480
The Seven Legends
are probably targeting you.

57
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:36,080
Until those seven are dealt with,

58
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:38,240
this deal doesn't start.

59
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,760
I know.

60
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,680
Their base is down there.

61
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:54,480
Follow my orders.

62
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,200
Juk. Dan.

63
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,120
‪Hey?!

64
00:06:58,000 --> 00:06:59,080
Where did everyone go?

65
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,960
Who's left?

66
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,000
Just me and Kuay.

67
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,760
What about the others?

68
00:07:06,960 --> 00:07:08,800
They know what to do.
We already had a briefing.

69
00:07:11,320 --> 00:07:12,200
Good.

70
00:07:14,360 --> 00:07:15,240
Moh.

71
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:16,880
Hello.

72
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:19,120
Hey, why are you shaking my hand?
Give me your gun.

73
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,800
You reached out.
I thought we were shaking hands.

74
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,920
How was I supposed to know?

75
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,640
You idiots…

76
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:29,560
Kuay, watch out.

77
00:07:32,560 --> 00:07:35,320
Here I am.

78
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,280
- Huh?
- The Seven Legends!

79
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,880
Kill them all. Go.

80
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,720
This place isn't safe anymore.

81
00:07:53,480 --> 00:07:54,480
Go!

82
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:05,240
Even if I didn't get my revenge on you,
the Seven Legends already did.

83
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,080
Dad! Dad!

84
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,280
Big mouth, aren't you?

85
00:08:12,320 --> 00:08:13,960
No need to go anywhere.
Just shoot them here.

86
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:17,400
Wait, wait! Hold on. You can kill me,

87
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,960
but let my daughter go. I'm begging you.

88
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:22,080
I'll definitely kill you.
But I'll take care of her myself.

89
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:26,280
Let Mook go. I'll give you however much
money you want. I've got plenty. Take it.

90
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:28,720
Your money? I'll take that for sure.

91
00:08:29,400 --> 00:08:31,960
But what I really want is your daughter.

92
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,559
- Come here.
- No!

93
00:08:33,640 --> 00:08:35,440
- Dad! Dad!
- No!

94
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,640
- Don't!
- Dad!

95
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:38,760
Dad!

96
00:08:43,559 --> 00:08:44,760
- Dad! Dad!
- Mook, come here.

97
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:52,960
Run, Mook.

98
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:55,400
- Dad.
- Serves you right.

99
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:59,080
Finally, you got betrayed by your people.
You'll tear each other apart in jail.

100
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:01,200
- Let me go!
- Dad.

101
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:04,920
Haven't you realized it yet?
Can't you change for me and Mom for once?

102
00:09:09,920 --> 00:09:10,760
Damn it.

103
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,600
Hey, let go.

104
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,000
Dad!

105
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:18,120
- Dad.
- You.

106
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:26,200
- Dad.
- Hey, Mook.

107
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,920
- Mook, run. I can't help you anymore.
- No. We'll go together.

108
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,080
- Mook, I'm sorry.
- Dad.

109
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,440
I'm sorry for everything.

110
00:09:33,520 --> 00:09:35,320
Sorry to you and Mom.

111
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,640
Don't let me be your burden.
Take her and run.

112
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:40,960
- No, go with me.
- Don't let me be your burden.

113
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:41,880
- No.
- They're coming.

114
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:44,040
- Go. Take her and run. Please.
- No.

115
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:45,480
- Please go, Ms. Mook.
- Go.

116
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,440
- Hurry up.
- Please go, dear.

117
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,680
Dad!

118
00:10:28,360 --> 00:10:29,960
Dad. Dad.

119
00:10:30,040 --> 00:10:32,880
- Dad. Dad. Dad.
- Ms. Mook. Ms. Mook.

120
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,200
- Dad.
- It's too late. Let's go.

121
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:36,920
- Dad.
- Let's go.

122
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,040
Arab.

123
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:11,320
Take cover!

124
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:15,680
Damn it.

125
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:22,120
Hold them off. I'll handle Arab myself.

126
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:25,840
- Sarge, can you handle him alone?
- Don't worry about me. Follow orders.

127
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:28,480
- Cover me!
- Sarge! Damn it.

128
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,480
- Kla, stop! I've got something good.
- What is it?

129
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:46,320
- Wow. Hurry up.
- Let's go.

130
00:11:56,080 --> 00:11:57,720
- Damn, there are so many of them.
- Crap.

131
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:00,560
What do we do?

132
00:12:00,640 --> 00:12:03,160
Hey! Are you ganging up on my little bros?

133
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,640
Have some of my dessert.

134
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:12,440
How's that? Sweet?

135
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:15,720
Heh. I'm Tueng, a desk officer outside
the Seven Legends plus one room.

136
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:22,280
- What?
- Thanks, Mr. Tueng. Your codename sucks.

137
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,600
Forget it. That's all I can think of.

138
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:26,920
Hey, they're coming.

139
00:12:36,760 --> 00:12:38,880
- There are a lot of them. Secretary Tueng.
- Yeah.

140
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:40,600
Radio Director Pantong.

141
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,640
- Send an airstrike. Now!
- Are you crazy?

142
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,520
This is a covert mission.

143
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:48,120
We've got one hour.
If you don't take them down,

144
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:49,560
we're all stuck here. We die here.

145
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,440
Get back to the comm unit.

146
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:56,120
- Call in the tanks to take them down. Go!
- Roger.

147
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:04,440
Damn. If they really bring tanks,

148
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:05,560
we're all dead for sure.

149
00:13:08,200 --> 00:13:09,360
Hey.

150
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,760
Listen. It won't come to that.

151
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,800
Let's do this.

152
00:13:14,920 --> 00:13:15,960
I'll make way with gunfire.

153
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,120
- Is that a good idea?
- Yeah. Go.

154
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:20,760
Don't worry. I'm all in.

155
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:24,040
You've got my back, I've got yours.
Deal? Hey?

156
00:13:24,680 --> 00:13:27,080
Where are you going?
Yeah, you're so worried about me.

157
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:34,200
Fine. Whatever happens, happens.
I, Secretary Tueng,

158
00:13:34,280 --> 00:13:37,080
will go down as a legend
with the Seven Legends. Come on!

159
00:13:39,080 --> 00:13:40,040
Come on!

160
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:46,840
- Moh, go check inside.
- Got it.

161
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,120
Hey, no one's here.

162
00:13:58,240 --> 00:13:59,400
Moh, go.

163
00:14:15,720 --> 00:14:19,560
Hey, hey. I've got a gun.

164
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:22,000
You wanna use knives?

165
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:24,760
Fine. You'd die too fast anyway.

166
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,240
I have mercy for animals.

167
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,280
Ow! A knee strike? No mercy at all.

168
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:08,960
Ow! Stop!

169
00:15:13,440 --> 00:15:14,760
Hey, hey, hey.

170
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,960
- Hey! Hm?
- Come on, come on.

171
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,720
Sorry, man.

172
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,240
- Ow!
- Hey, what's wrong?

173
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,080
- I got stabbed.
- Oh, yeah?

174
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:50,440
- Hey, I'll help.
- No, no! I'll be bleeding.

175
00:15:50,520 --> 00:15:51,600
Then I'm putting it back in.

176
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:53,200
Ouch!

177
00:15:53,280 --> 00:15:55,440
Hang in there. Go to the hospital, okay?

178
00:15:55,520 --> 00:15:56,640
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

179
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,200
Arab.

180
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:14,120
Hey. Call for reinforcements.
Get a tank here, now.

181
00:16:16,040 --> 00:16:18,800
Hey! I said get a tank.

182
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,520
I said call the tank in!

183
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,680
Get the tank now!

184
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,640
Why are you yelling?

185
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:31,560
That's it. Be right back!

186
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,680
What? Two sacks of rice?

187
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:38,400
Not rice, tank! Yeah, I know!

188
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:40,880
Oh?

189
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:45,720
Tank. It must be urgent.

190
00:16:45,800 --> 00:16:48,080
It has to be urgent
if I'm calling in a tank.

191
00:16:48,160 --> 00:16:50,800
I'm calling in a tank for you right now!
Come on, Tank.

192
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:52,040
Where's the tank?

193
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:53,880
Damn it, you…

194
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:55,200
Hm?

195
00:16:55,280 --> 00:16:56,440
Is your tank coming?

196
00:16:58,560 --> 00:17:00,160
- Go on, radio it.
- Yeah, call it.

197
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:01,520
You got the guts?

198
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,080
- The tank?
- Mm.

199
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,680
No.

200
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:06,760
- Hm.
- Hm.

201
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:17,440
He forgot his underwear.

202
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,880
And you're grabbing it? Hey!

203
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,680
Oh, he's coming back for it.

204
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:32,400
Feels like someone's behind us.

205
00:17:36,840 --> 00:17:38,320
- New guy?
- He's huge.

206
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:53,920
Uh!

207
00:18:12,720 --> 00:18:14,280
Come here.

208
00:18:20,560 --> 00:18:21,400
‪Akki.

209
00:18:23,440 --> 00:18:25,480
Hey, we're here to help.

210
00:18:26,040 --> 00:18:26,880
What?

211
00:18:29,240 --> 00:18:30,400
You two can't handle him?

212
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:31,960
Mm. You try.

213
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:35,520
You're just kids. Watch me.

214
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:39,520
No need. I got this.

215
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,760
- I don't need a gun.
- Go on, man.

216
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:44,640
How hard can it be?

217
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:51,840
- Damn. You're another kid.
- Don't go. Trust me.

218
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:57,680
Told you.

219
00:19:00,320 --> 00:19:01,480
- Moh.
- Huh?

220
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:03,760
Is that a person or an AI?

221
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,760
One, two, three.

222
00:19:16,120 --> 00:19:18,480
- Still.
- Still?

223
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,080
You guys are still not helping me.

224
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,360
Oh?

225
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:23,520
- Aren't you so tough? Go on.
- Yeah.

226
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:24,640
I'm done, buddy.

227
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,920
Tangkuay, let's go Chinese boxing.

228
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,640
- Full brawl.
- That's my style, man.

229
00:19:52,560 --> 00:19:53,680
Get up.

230
00:19:55,720 --> 00:19:56,920
You think you're tough?

231
00:19:59,080 --> 00:20:00,520
So tough, huh?

232
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:04,960
Take these.

233
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,960
Guys, let's just finish him.

234
00:20:08,040 --> 00:20:08,880
Mm.

235
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:12,680
- Come on. One, two, three.
- Come on.

236
00:20:23,920 --> 00:20:24,840
What a tough dude.

237
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:30,840
Hey.

238
00:20:31,920 --> 00:20:33,000
Blood?

239
00:20:33,640 --> 00:20:34,920
Think I'm really tough?

240
00:20:39,560 --> 00:20:40,840
All done. He's down.

241
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,960
Don't tell anyone we got lucky.
That was four against one.

242
00:20:48,040 --> 00:20:50,000
- So embarrassing.
- Just between us.

243
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,520
- Okay.
- Let's move.

244
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:53,600
Juk should've planted bombs
everywhere by now.

245
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,600
- Go.
- Go.

246
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:00,200
- Got it. Go.
- Go.

247
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,720
- Go.
- Go.

248
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:19,080
Are you okay?

249
00:21:27,960 --> 00:21:29,280
How is it? All set?

250
00:21:29,360 --> 00:21:31,480
All set, bro. Bombs planted at every spot.

251
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:32,400
Good.

252
00:21:37,280 --> 00:21:38,120
Hey.

253
00:21:39,720 --> 00:21:40,920
Let's go.

254
00:21:58,840 --> 00:21:59,760
Arab!

255
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,440
Drop your weapon and surrender.
You're done.

256
00:22:08,240 --> 00:22:09,200
Wait.

257
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:15,480
What are you doing
with that remote? Watching TV?

258
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:17,840
You'll see.

259
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:20,760
Hey, that's a detonator!

260
00:22:32,320 --> 00:22:35,960
Arab, are you scared of me?
Why are you using bombs?

261
00:22:37,480 --> 00:22:39,560
Just fight me head-on.

262
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:42,080
You're about to face
my Dab the Red Inferno move.

263
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,840
Give me one more shot.

264
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,840
I swear I'll blow your head off.

265
00:22:46,480 --> 00:22:47,520
All right.

266
00:22:58,560 --> 00:22:59,880
Sarge Dab!

267
00:23:27,880 --> 00:23:29,360
Is that all you've got?

268
00:23:31,280 --> 00:23:32,480
Wait a sec.

269
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,560
Still have your doubts?

270
00:23:51,480 --> 00:23:52,680
Behind you.

271
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,600
I've been curious for a while.

272
00:24:07,320 --> 00:24:08,560
Why a school uniform?

273
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:23,600
Hurry up. Run.

274
00:24:25,120 --> 00:24:26,480
Take cover! Go!

275
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:28,920
Take cover, Ms. Mook.

276
00:24:37,760 --> 00:24:39,000
‪Let's go.

277
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,040
- How are you?
- Are you safe?

278
00:24:41,120 --> 00:24:42,720
- You all right?
- You okay?

279
00:24:48,720 --> 00:24:50,320
- Boss, Arab is dead.
- Huh?

280
00:24:50,400 --> 00:24:51,560
The base's been overrun too.

281
00:24:53,720 --> 00:24:56,280
Arab's dead and the base's overrun?

282
00:24:56,360 --> 00:24:58,240
Damn it.

283
00:24:58,880 --> 00:25:02,040
Don't tell me the goods I prepared
for the deal got seized too.

284
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:04,600
What a waste of time.

285
00:25:05,640 --> 00:25:08,280
Hey, Sergey, calm down.

286
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:10,080
Give me a little more time.

287
00:25:12,680 --> 00:25:15,120
Cancel the whole deal.
My plane is waiting.

288
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:18,360
- Let's go.
- Wait, then let me go with you.

289
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:22,480
The Seven Legends
just interfered with this deal.

290
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:24,440
There are plenty
of other profitable deals.

291
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:27,440
- We'll talk on the plane.
- I made a mistake.

292
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:29,400
I thought you were a professional.

293
00:25:30,080 --> 00:25:32,320
Turns out you're just an amateur.
Pathetic.

294
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,320
Watch your mouth.

295
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:39,040
Hey, hey.

296
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,520
Why did you do this?

297
00:25:44,920 --> 00:25:46,840
Plenty of people
probably want to take you down.

298
00:26:00,920 --> 00:26:02,200
Stop!

299
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:12,520
So the Phoenix finally ended up
a broken-winged bird.

300
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:15,360
You're under arrest, Sriwong.

301
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:23,000
Colonel, please take Sriwong
into custody at headquarters.

302
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:25,520
- I'll head back to base to see my father.
- Okay.

303
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:26,680
Take him.

304
00:26:34,200 --> 00:26:35,400
Be careful.

305
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:49,400
- You're all right now.
- Be careful.

306
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:50,920
This is the end.

307
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:54,520
- Juk.
- Yes?

308
00:26:54,600 --> 00:26:55,520
You planted the bombs?

309
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,560
- All set, bro. Just a sec.
- Yeah.

310
00:26:57,640 --> 00:27:00,440
Alright then, blow it up, bro.

311
00:27:00,520 --> 00:27:01,840
Sure, bro.

312
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,000
- Hey, wait, wait!
- Woo.

313
00:27:03,080 --> 00:27:04,680
Hold on!

314
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:08,240
- Blowing up what? Trying to kill me?
- Where've you been, Sarge?

315
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,120
- Yeah.
- Is everything all right?

316
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:11,560
- All good.
- Hey.

317
00:27:11,640 --> 00:27:14,000
We need a little ceremony,
like lighting fireworks.

318
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,200
- Sit, sit.
- Mm.

319
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:17,920
Sit down.

320
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:23,640
We'll do a countdown ritual.
Count to a hundred.

321
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:25,680
- One.
- That's too long.

322
00:27:25,760 --> 00:27:27,640
- That's too long, Sarge.
- Yeah.

323
00:27:28,560 --> 00:27:31,080
Let's count to three. Three, two, one.

324
00:27:32,440 --> 00:27:34,920
- Yeah.
- Okay. Three, two, one. Detonate.

325
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:36,120
- Ready?
- Yes.

326
00:27:36,200 --> 00:27:37,560
Three.

327
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:51,680
Just three and boom. No two, no one.

328
00:27:52,480 --> 00:27:54,160
Director Pantong told us

329
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:55,920
to finish the mission within four hours.

330
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:57,320
You all did great.

331
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:59,840
Let's head back to the motherland.

332
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,400
Stop!

333
00:28:11,560 --> 00:28:13,440
Easy, bro. We're on the same side.

334
00:28:27,360 --> 00:28:29,000
Hey, Ms. Khim.

335
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:32,400
Oh, wow.

336
00:28:34,600 --> 00:28:36,200
- Woohoo.
- Hm.

337
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:39,640
I told you, I won't leave you
as a bride without her groom.

338
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:44,760
- Try leaving her hanging, you'll see.
- Hey.

339
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:46,520
- Ouch.
- You'll cut it?

340
00:28:46,600 --> 00:28:48,360
Hey. Scissors won't cut.

341
00:28:51,760 --> 00:28:52,720
Hey, dramatic scene over here.

342
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,960
- Hey.
- Come look.

343
00:29:06,600 --> 00:29:09,120
I'm sorry about your father.

344
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,800
My dad's path
didn't have many possible endings.

345
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:16,280
Mom and I were prepared.

346
00:29:18,640 --> 00:29:19,640
It's okay.

347
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:22,120
From now on, I'll take care of you.

348
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:29,240
Thank you, Mr. Dan.

349
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:32,120
But…

350
00:29:32,800 --> 00:29:35,040
I promised my mother

351
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:36,960
I'd take her to live in England.

352
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:42,400
Uh, don't forget to exchange for pounds.

353
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:48,800
You really have to go?

354
00:29:50,520 --> 00:29:51,440
Yes.

355
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:55,040
After what my dad did, I can't stay here.

356
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:02,240
Thank you, everyone, for everything.

357
00:30:17,680 --> 00:30:18,960
- Whoa.
- Oh?

358
00:30:25,720 --> 00:30:27,080
What does that mean?

359
00:30:28,520 --> 00:30:31,440
When the time is right, we'll meet again.

360
00:30:36,880 --> 00:30:38,680
Look, look, look.

361
00:30:38,760 --> 00:30:39,680
- Look.
- Yeah.

362
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:45,160
Oh.

363
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:58,120
Thank you all.

364
00:30:58,680 --> 00:31:00,880
Phoenix has been detained
with solid evidence.

365
00:31:00,960 --> 00:31:02,080
- Yes.
- Yes.

366
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:07,080
It's unfortunate that none of your names
will be recorded in the system.

367
00:31:08,920 --> 00:31:12,840
But you've proven
that you are real heroes.

368
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:16,640
The hero was always inside you.

369
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:20,480
Mr. Poramate was right to choose you
to carry on the name of the Seven Legends.

370
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,920
Congratulations to all of you.

371
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:29,320
As agreed,
you'll each receive what you asked for.

372
00:31:31,480 --> 00:31:34,160
Your positions reinstated,

373
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:37,320
promotions, and reward money.

374
00:31:37,400 --> 00:31:40,920
- Yeah!
- That's nice.

375
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:42,320
- Reward money too.
- Except one person.

376
00:31:43,480 --> 00:31:45,400
- Dan?
- Huh? Not me.

377
00:31:45,480 --> 00:31:47,520
- Definitely not me.
- Tangkuay for sure.

378
00:31:47,600 --> 00:31:49,600
- Kla?
- I've never done anything wrong.

379
00:31:49,680 --> 00:31:50,680
- You?
- Never.

380
00:31:50,760 --> 00:31:52,760
- I need money.
- Kla.

381
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,280
I'm not as bad as you.

382
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,760
That's not true.

383
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:57,200
Sergeant Dab Jampoh.

384
00:31:57,280 --> 00:31:59,200
- Sergeant Dab, yeah. Huh?
- Oh.

385
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:00,360
Oh?

386
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:02,880
- Not us.
- Oh, my.

387
00:32:03,560 --> 00:32:06,160
Sergeant Dab
must first face disciplinary action.

388
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:11,160
During the mission
you violated multiple orders.

389
00:32:11,240 --> 00:32:14,600
If you only reward and never punish,
the system falls apart.

390
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:16,800
- Whoa.
- I knew it.

391
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,520
Wait, Net.

392
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,960
No, Dad. Rules are rules.

393
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,320
Come with me, Sergeant.

394
00:32:26,280 --> 00:32:27,800
Come receive your disciplinary order.

395
00:32:33,160 --> 00:32:35,080
Whoa.

396
00:32:35,160 --> 00:32:38,320
- You're done for.
- You're done for, Sarge.

397
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:39,640
If I get punished,

398
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:41,000
I'll come back and deal with all of you.

399
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:42,920
- Ouch.
- Ow.

400
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,560
- Hey, hey.
- Sarge.

401
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:47,880
- You're done for.
- Come tell us what happens.

402
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:10,240
What punishment are you giving me?

403
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,480
Hey, hey.

404
00:33:15,080 --> 00:33:18,160
Your gravest offense

405
00:33:18,240 --> 00:33:20,040
was misconduct toward a superior officer.

406
00:33:20,760 --> 00:33:23,920
Therefore,
the most appropriate punishment is…

407
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:26,040
Are you going to kill me?

408
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,760
Fine. I've survived so many times already.

409
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:33,360
If I die by a beautiful woman's hand,
so be it.

410
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:48,520
Hey.

411
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,760
Right here? For real?

412
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:54,040
- Okay.
- Hey, Sarge. What are you doing?

413
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:56,600
Oh?

414
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:59,040
Didn't you want to see
my Dab the Red Inferno move?

415
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:01,760
Well, I heard it's impressive.

416
00:34:01,840 --> 00:34:02,960
Hey.

417
00:34:03,040 --> 00:34:07,080
Impressive? That's an understatement.
I've got a secret move nobody's seen.

418
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:09,360
You're being cheeky.

419
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,199
Behave yourself.

420
00:34:16,760 --> 00:34:20,199
You can behave yourself.
You saved the country.

421
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,880
Remember what I told you?

422
00:34:23,480 --> 00:34:26,400
- If you fixed your bad habits…
- I'd win your heart, right?

423
00:34:34,280 --> 00:34:35,760
Right? Right?

424
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:45,280
I remember everything you said.

425
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:01,960
Let me ask you guys something.
Do you regret it?

426
00:35:02,040 --> 00:35:04,360
We've risked our lives like that.

427
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:06,520
In the end, it's like
gilding the back of the Buddha,

428
00:35:07,400 --> 00:35:08,920
Even if we're just gilding the back,

429
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,800
if you walk around,
you still see the gold.

430
00:35:13,320 --> 00:35:14,520
Juk's right.

431
00:35:15,200 --> 00:35:18,480
But we even gilded under the base.

432
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:21,960
You'd have to lift the statue to see it.

433
00:35:23,560 --> 00:35:27,040
Honestly,
I've wanted to say this for a while.

434
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,800
- Don't tell me…
- You're going to say you love us?

435
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:32,280
What's wrong with you?

436
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:35,040
I love all of you.

437
00:35:35,120 --> 00:35:37,440
- Yeah.
- Woo.

438
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:39,040
I feel the same.

439
00:35:39,800 --> 00:35:42,920
I'm really glad I met you guys

440
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:44,320
and got to be your friend.

441
00:35:46,160 --> 00:35:47,800
Stop pushing me.

442
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:49,600
- Same here.
- Hey.

443
00:35:49,680 --> 00:35:51,200
- Here we go.
- Under heaven,

444
00:35:51,280 --> 00:35:54,400
nothing is more important
than comrades who live and die together.

445
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:58,680
- Me too. I feel like…
- Yeah.

446
00:35:58,760 --> 00:36:02,400
…we've risked everything,
been through heat and cold, bombs,

447
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:04,200
- bullets, and many things.
- Yeah.

448
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:05,920
- Yeah, true.
- But we're still standing.

449
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:06,920
- Oh.
- That's awesome.

450
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:10,680
Of course we're awesome.
Otherwise, we wouldn't have survived.

451
00:36:10,760 --> 00:36:12,000
- But it doesn't mean…
- Here it comes.

452
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:14,480
- Here we go.
- …that we're stopping here, right?

453
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:16,160
Yeah.

454
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,400
You're looking cool.

455
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:19,400
Yeah.

456
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:24,400
Because no one else
can write a new legend like we can.

457
00:36:24,480 --> 00:36:27,720
None of us was born a hero.

458
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:31,480
But the world needs ordinary people
who never give up, like us.

459
00:36:37,240 --> 00:36:38,360
Come on.

460
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:48,080
We all have to stay ready.

461
00:36:48,880 --> 00:36:52,120
There are still scumbags like Phoenix
waiting for us to take them down.

462
00:36:54,200 --> 00:36:55,160
Cool, right?

463
00:36:56,400 --> 00:36:59,480
So cool.

464
00:36:59,560 --> 00:37:01,120
We're all cool.

465
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:40,480
THE END

466
00:38:06,080 --> 00:38:09,160
TWO MONTHS LATER

467
00:38:10,240 --> 00:38:12,080
- Where are you going?
- Sit down.

468
00:38:12,160 --> 00:38:14,520
Sit down. Come on.

469
00:38:14,600 --> 00:38:17,000
Whoa, that bad? What happened?

470
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:18,760
Come on.

471
00:38:18,840 --> 00:38:20,520
Come on.

472
00:38:22,360 --> 00:38:23,600
- What's wrong?
- What's wrong, Dan?

473
00:38:24,640 --> 00:38:26,880
You remember Ms. Mookda?

474
00:38:27,920 --> 00:38:29,720
- She's gone.
- Gone where?

475
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:32,960
She ran off with a foreign husband.
She got herself a foreign husband!

476
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:39,200
- Two-timing woman!
- Ooh.

477
00:38:40,760 --> 00:38:44,600
I'm gonna beat him up. I'll fly to England
and stomp that blond white dude.

478
00:38:44,680 --> 00:38:46,320
- He's mad.
- I'll beat him up.

479
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:48,520
Calm down.

480
00:38:48,600 --> 00:38:50,360
- You can't.
- The only problem is, I don't have money.

481
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:52,000
Yeah, I know.

482
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:04,880
I'm about to close.

483
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:07,840
- I'd like…
- Uh.

484
00:39:07,920 --> 00:39:09,560
- Can I have <i>larb</i>?
- No need to order.

485
00:39:09,640 --> 00:39:11,720
I'll make it for you.

486
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:14,240
- Okay?
- Okay.

487
00:39:14,320 --> 00:39:16,000
- No beef.
- No pork either.

488
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:18,680
- No meatballs.
- He's got a lot of things.

489
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:27,200
I'm not here for revenge.

490
00:39:27,280 --> 00:39:29,080
Damn, he speaks Thai too.

491
00:39:29,880 --> 00:39:32,080
I've got a job for you.

492
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:33,200
Oh?

493
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:36,040
A world-class mafia like you
has work for us?

494
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:41,280
<i>Urgent report. There's been a bombing</i>
<i>attack on the convoy of Mr. Komsan,</i>

495
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:46,000
<i>the Deputy Prime Minister, while he was on</i>
<i>his way to a regional cooperation summit.</i>

496
00:39:46,080 --> 00:39:48,080
<i>There are many injured.</i>

497
00:39:48,160 --> 00:39:49,760
- Mm. Whoa.
- Careful.

498
00:39:50,280 --> 00:39:53,840
My boss has been captured.
If you rescue him,

499
00:39:53,920 --> 00:39:55,760
you'll get information

500
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:59,320
on who bombed your Deputy PM's convoy.

501
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,560
Hold on.

502
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,400
Something feels off.

503
00:40:13,240 --> 00:40:15,680
He smiled like a Thai soap opera villain.

504
00:40:15,760 --> 00:40:18,120
- Like who?
- Oliver Beaver.

505
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:21,360
- Hey, what's that? Open it first.
- Open it.

506
00:40:24,520 --> 00:40:27,160
- Dan.
- I've got money to go to England now!

507
00:40:28,720 --> 00:40:29,840
Wait.

508
00:40:30,520 --> 00:40:33,080
- The first one is real. The rest are fake.
- Huh?

509
00:40:33,680 --> 00:40:35,200
Hey!

510
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:38,440
Bomb!

511
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:57,040
Ouch.

512
00:40:58,160 --> 00:41:00,200
Woohoo!

513
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,560
- Didn't hit me at all.
- Okay.

514
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:02,880
Igor's here.

515
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,040
Stand up. Draw your guns.

516
00:41:04,120 --> 00:41:06,400
- Hey, the mafia's here!
- Hey, hey.

517
00:41:21,320 --> 00:41:23,920
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
